Sensitive personal data revealing racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religious or philosophical beliefs, or trade union membership, and the processing of genetic data, biometric data for the purpose of uniquely identifying you, data concerning your health or data concerning your sex life or sexual orientation, shall not be collected, except when consented to, carried out in the course of StockKnowledge’s legitimate activities with appropriate safeguards, necessary in the interest of the public, or for scientific, historical research or statistical purposes.<br>
Any sensitive personal information collected combined with Personal Information will be treated as Personal Information.<br>
Any information that we collect from you shall be processed lawfully, fairly and in a transparent manner. It shall only be collected for specified, explicit and legitimate purposes and shall not be further processed in a manner that is incompatible with those purposes. Collection shall be adequate, relevant and limited to what is necessary in relation to the purposes for which they are processed. Information collected shall be treated with integrity and confidentiality.</p>
<p class="has-line-data" data-line-start="21" data-line-end="28">Your Profile, Community Forums and User Content<br>
You may have the opportunity to create a profile, which consists of information about you, which may include Personal Information, photographs, information about your academic and work history, your interests and activities, your use of the Services and other information (“Profile”). Some of the information in your Profile may be visible to third parties or to everyone, depending on the nature of the information and the privacy settings you choose when you sign in to your account on the Service where you created your Profile. Your Profile may also be indexed by and displayed by internet search providers when someone searches for your name. Stock Knowledge does not control how frequently third-party search engines update their indexes; consequently, their information may be outdated and still available for a period of time even if you discontinue use of the Service.<br>
Note that in order to provide services and opportunities to you, educational organizations and other third parties may be able to review certain information in your Profile for some of the Services, whether or not you have limited public access to that information. You may have the opportunity to control whether this information is shared, but some information may be shared automatically — all as disclosed on the web site or other service where you created your Profile. Stock Knowledge does not share your contact information (email, full postal address or phone number) with those third parties unless you request or agree to that sharing. However, Stock Knowledge may send you information and offers from third parties and information about the Services, and you may not be able to opt-out from these messages without closing your account.<br>
